{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"32132417-5915-44cf-935d-1353b8cb2f66","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nThe `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package works with the **Microsoft Testing Platform** (which your project uses via `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`). Hot reload requires the test host process to stay alive and watch for changes, which is what `dotnet run` does — it launches the test executable directly.\n\n`dotnet test` spawns a separate process and exits, so it won't keep the hot reload watcher active.\n\nRun it like:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj\n```\n\nThen edit your test or source files, and the runner will automatically re-execute affected tests.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9be302bd-2ec0-4ebd-8373-a3ff831ab2fc","outputTokens":160,"requestId":"BD05:26F972:1C31518:1FBA059:6A07C0B5"},"id":"f09c84ec-3514-43ed-ac5d-79e69143e0d7","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:56:27.096Z","parentId":"76784e6c-6221-4a7f-912a-ed472349f935"}
